libmdr (0.7.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * deb build fixes for quilt
  * Reload CRLs on change
  * Fine tune error handling
  * Be more strict about the number of array members passed to pack/unpack
  * Log when we reload a CRL
  * New function to get the length of a spec's vector, useful for stack array
    sizes
  * Fix bad deref
  * On OpenBSD, we get X509_V_ERR_UNABLE_TO_GET_ISSUER_CERT_LOCALLY during our
    tests for self-signed certs, so allow it when we don't require valid certs
  * If we have coredumps enabled, don't chdir
  * Fix leak on session close initiated by the backend
  * Make sure we don't purge session in use by the current mdrd_recvhdl,
    if provided
  * Relax check in pack/unpack on the length of the mdr vector; make sure it
    is large enough
  * Make sure we can't pass a NULL spec to pmdr_pack()

 -- Pascal Lalonde <plalonde@overnet.ca>  Wed, 06 May 2026 10:57:36 -0400

